awards.description:
The High Potential Talent Program aims at identifying and cultivating outstanding employees, equipped with the skills and capabilities to hold future leadership positions. It focuses on leadership skills, such as strategic thinking, managing collaboration and coping with high levels of complexity.

Objectives:
- Exposure to strategic views;
- Giving knowledge and skills at the organizational and personal level;
- Establishing a good networking group as a model for collaboration;
- Supporting personal development.

profile_positions.description:
▪ Managing two teams, in charge of B2B activities in EU, split by product:
--- PTW (Power Two Wheeler), namely Motorcycles and Scooters, and related sub-groups, like engines or specific accessories;
--- EPAC (Electric Power Assisted Cycle), namely pedal assisted e-kits.
▪ OEM key account:
--- Troopy, for scooter sharing activities;
--- Fantic Motor, for the supply of rolling chassis, enduro and cross motorcycles;
--- GEO TECHNOLOGY and BeOn, for the supply of motorcycle engines to be used for GP moto3 and pre-moto3 classes;
--- Mygale, for the supply of motorcycle engines to be used on FIA entry class of racing cross 4-wheeler;
--- E-bicycle manufacturers, for the supply of PAS e-kits, like Accell group and PEXCO;
▪ New technologies, future mobility and trends:
--- EV development: analyzing current and future share of EVs in the global production of vehicles, incorporating key components such as e-motors and batteries or charging infrastructure deployment.
--- EV adoption: discussing key challenges in the transition to e-mobility and solutions that are well suited to address topics like ownership cost, policy frameworks and market systems.
--- EV application: interplay among electric, shared and automated mobility options.
